        <headline>Flood Advisory issued June 27 at 5:15PM CDT until June 27 at 8:15PM CDT by NWS St Louis MO</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...Portions of Illinois, including the following counties,
northwestern Calhoun and central southeastern Pike and northeast
Missouri, including the following county, central southeastern
Pike.

* WHEN...Until 815 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 515 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin
shortly in the advisory area. Between 1 and 3 inches of rain
have fallen.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Bowling Green, Louisiana, Pleasant Hill, Clarksville,
Frankford, Pike, Curryville, Tarrants, Belleview,
Independence, Martinsburg and Nebo.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
